stories.title: Bracewell completes the jigsaw
stories.subTitle: Exciting times for New Zealand
stories.summary: There haven't been many moments in New Zealand's cricket history when there has been the chance to believe, firmly, that when the side takes the field its prospects of victory are better than 50%

stories.title: Vettori inspires 107-run victory
stories.subTitle: N Zealand v West Indies, NatWest Series final, Lord's
stories.summary: Daniel Vettori gave a virtuoso exhibition of the left-arm spinner's art, and rifled in throws with the accuracy of a knife-thrower as New Zealand romped to a 107-run victory over West Indies in the final of the NatWest Series at Lord's
